Round 1: 
[Patient] "What foods can I eat to help manage my heart failure?" 
[Educator] "Focus on lean proteins like chicken and fish." 

Round 2: 
[Patient] "Are there any vegetables that are good for my heart?" 
[Educator] "Yes, include leafy greens like spinach and kale in your diet." 

Round 3: 
[Patient] "Can I still have fruits with heart failure?" 
[Educator] "Yes, opt for fruits like berries and apples in moderation." 

Round 4: 
[Patient] "Should I avoid any specific types of fats?" 
[Educator] "Limit saturated fats found in red meat and processed foods." 

Round 5: 
[Patient] "Are there any drinks I should avoid with heart failure?" 
[Educator] "Limit your intake of sugary beverages and opt for water or unsweetened tea."